1 0 0 1 56 644.0 Tm (Between the reigns of Edward III and Henry IV the silver content of the English penny) Tj
1 0 0 1 56 630.0 Tm (declined in a series of poorly documented adjustments. Drawing on mint indentures, hoard) Tj
1 0 0 1 56 616.0 Tm (analysis, and the neglected records of the Tower assay, this paper reconstructs the sequence) Tj
1 0 0 1 56 602.0 Tm (of debasements and distinguishes deliberate fiscal manipulation by the Crown from the slow) Tj
1 0 0 1 56 588.0 Tm (erosion of weight caused by clipping and ordinary wear. I argue that contemporaries) Tj
1 0 0 1 56 574.0 Tm (understood the difference perfectly well, and that the language of 'sweating' coin in court) Tj
1 0 0 1 56 560.0 Tm (records is evidence of a sophisticated popular theory of money.) Tj
