/F1 10 Tf
1 0 0 1 56 514.0 Tm (The medieval penny was a remarkably stable object for most of its life, and that stability) Tj
1 0 0 1 56 500.0 Tm (is precisely why its periods of instability repay study. A coin that is expected to hold its) Tj
1 0 0 1 56 486.0 Tm (weight becomes, when it does not, a sensitive instrument for reading the fiscal pressures on) Tj
1 0 0 1 56 472.0 Tm (the state that issues it.) Tj
1 0 0 1 56 458.0 Tm () Tj
1 0 0 1 56 444.0 Tm (This paper covers the seventy-odd years from the great recoinage of Edward III to the end of) Tj
1 0 0 1 56 430.0 Tm (Henry IV's reign, a window in which the standard penny lost an appreciable fraction of its) Tj
1 0 0 1 56 416.0 Tm (silver. The challenge is to separate official debasement, decided in council and executed at) Tj
1 0 0 1 56 402.0 Tm (the mint, from the diffuse private debasement worked by clippers and sweaters on coins) Tj
1 0 0 1 56 388.0 Tm (already in circulation.) Tj
