/F1 10 Tf
1 0 0 1 56 342.0 Tm (Mint indentures, the contracts between the Crown and the master of the mint, nominally fix) Tj
1 0 0 1 56 328.0 Tm (the weight and fineness of new coin. They are the obvious starting point, but they record) Tj
1 0 0 1 56 314.0 Tm (intention rather than outcome. An indenture that specifies a lighter penny tells us the) Tj
1 0 0 1 56 300.0 Tm (Crown chose to debase; it does not tell us how much lighter the coins in a labourer's purse) Tj
1 0 0 1 56 286.0 Tm (actually were a decade later.) Tj
1 0 0 1 56 272.0 Tm () Tj
1 0 0 1 56 258.0 Tm (For that we must turn to hoards. The buried savings of the anxious are the social) Tj
1 0 0 1 56 244.0 Tm (historian's good fortune, and three hoards from the period, weighed coin by coin, allow a) Tj
1 0 0 1 56 230.0 Tm (direct comparison between the legal standard and the circulating reality. The gap between) Tj
1 0 0 1 56 216.0 Tm (them is the measure of private erosion.) Tj
1 0 0 1 56 202.0 Tm () Tj
