1 0 0 1 56 184.0 Tm (Clipping versus Sweating) Tj
/F1 10 Tf
1 0 0 1 56 170.0 Tm (Two illicit techniques degraded coin in opposite styles. Clipping shaved metal from the rim) Tj
1 0 0 1 56 156.0 Tm (and left a visibly smaller coin; it was crude, profitable, and easy to detect once milled) Tj
1 0 0 1 56 142.0 Tm (edges were a distant invention. Sweating was subtler: coins were sealed in a bag and shaken) Tj
1 0 0 1 56 128.0 Tm (until a fine dust of silver abraded from their surfaces, leaving each individual piece) Tj
1 0 0 1 56 114.0 Tm (almost unchanged while the bag's owner accumulated a small fortune in metal.) Tj
1 0 0 1 56 100.0 Tm () Tj
1 0 0 1 56 86.0 Tm (Court records distinguish the two offences with a precision that surprised earlier) Tj
1 0 0 1 56 72.0 Tm (historians. The vocabulary of 'sweating' appears in indictments well before any royal) Tj
